d one community to host two landfills and made Michigan a leading importer of foreign waste. Focusing on local activists opposed to the transnational waste trade with Canada, the book’s ethnography analyzes their attempts to politicize the removal of waste out of sight that many take for granted. Documenting these different ways of relating to the management of North American rubbish, Waste Away demonstrates how the landfills we create remake us in turn, often behind our backs and beneath our notice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRefuse and refuse disposalxSocial aspectszNorth America. 0aSanitary landfillsxSocial aspectszMichigan. 0aSanitary landfillszMichiganzDetroit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerican waste.  abundling waste.  adetroit landfill.  adetroit.  adirty jobs.  adiscard studies.  adump.  aforeign waste.  agarbage collection.  agarbage disposal.  agarbage men.  ahistory of garbage in the us.  aimported waste.  alandfills.  anorth american landfills.  apolitical economy.  arefuse collection.  arefuse studies.  asanitary landfill.  atransnational waste.  atrash collector.  atrash disposal.  atrash heap.  atrash men.  awaste disposal.  awaste management.  awaste workers.  aworking class jobs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028893540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096377140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963771423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963771/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY